Rider to Part 9b of LM-10 for Fiscal year 2004
In the year 2004, more specifically during the Christmas season, this firm forwarded traditional
Christmas holiday cheer baskets, consisting of fruit, cheeses, etc. to all of its regular clients and
former clients, some of whom are officers of labor organizations. We did not retain specific
records of the individuals to whom they were sent. Additionally, during the NFL season, on a
sporadic basis, we would offer the use of tickets to New York Giants or Jets football games.
This offer was made to friends, retainer clients, former clients and periodic clients. We did not
retain specific records regarding the persons who were afforded use of our season tickets, some
of whom were officers of various labor organizations.
The value of each holiday gift basket was approximately $100.00 - $125.00 each. Similarly, the
cost of a ticket to a football game was approximately $50.00 - $75.00 per ticket. We wish to
emphasize that these courtesies were extended to all regular clients including but not limited to
